*** Please click on "Listings by this user" to see more of my items for multi guns trade. ***

The Ruger Police Carbine is a pistol caliber carbine designed as a companion to the Ruger P Series pistols. As of 2007, Ruger has discontinued production. It is a semi-automatic carbine using a blowback action. The Carbine uses the same ammunition and magazines as the Ruger P Series 9mm and .40 S&W caliber pistols.

Both the PC9 (the 9mm version) and the PC4 (.40 S&W) are patterned after the highly successful Ruger 10/22 carbine. The Carbine is intended as a shoulder weapon for police use, although it is available for sale to civilians as well. The intent is that an officer will carry a Ruger P Series pistol as a sidearm, and keep a Carbine available (for example, in his/her patrol vehicle) as a shoulder weapon if needed. Since the carbine has a 16-inch (410 mm) barrel, it provides more power with the same ammunition used by the 4-inch (100 mm) barreled pistol. The carbine also provides additional accuracy and range over the pistol.

title: For Sale:  Remington 870 Bullpup conversion
postcontent:
Selling my Bullpup SG. Interstate Arms Hawk 981R in a Bullpup Unlimited Remington 870 SG Kit with upgrades.
This has been my Home Defense weapon for about a year or so. Because of it's compact design, it lets you maneuver around corners without exposing part of your weapon.  , unnecessarily. It eats everything you feed it in 2 3/4 and 3 inch shells. If you have an AR, you will like the trigger, safety selector, and angle grip.

The SG: I chose the Interstate Arms 981R as my platform as it is an identical clone of the Rem 870.  The only difference found between the two, is in the barrel. In every other aspect it resembles the Rem 870. I searched the internet and found plenty of positive information on the Hawk 981R and the bullpup kit before starting the project.

The kit: It simple and solid. The kit makes a Remington 870, go from 38.25 inches in length to 28.5 inches. AR style grip, trigger, and selector switch. Remington recoil pad takes a ton of the kick off. 15.5 inches of picatinny rail on top lets you place your optic wherever you want it. It has two, 2.5 picatinny rails on both sides to attach a light or anything else.

Here's the list of the whole conversion plus upgrades cost:

Hawk 981R SG - $172
Bullpup Kit - $295
Wilson Combat Extension - $42 
Fab Defense Side Saddle - $ $32
Bullpup Unlimited 90 degree side rail - $10

I have a Cobra Tactical Systems ergo grip that I will throw in for an extra $20.

title: For Sale:  Rifle Dynamics AK 5.45
postcontent:
I am regretfully selling my Rifle Dynamics AK. 

I originally purchased this rifle as a 5.45x39 Saiga that Century had converted the back end of the rifle on. I fired about 300 rounds through it in that configuration, then sent it into Rifle Dynamics to have the whole rifle worked over and made amazing. They went through the whole rifle and smoothed it up, made sure everything was tight and right and straight, they removed the accessory rail from the side, installed their trademark Bolton gas block/sight combo, cut the barrel down and pinned/welded a Smith Vortex flash hider for an OAL of 16.1 inches. They bead blasted the whole gun down to bare metal, parkerized it and then coated it in their gray Norrell's moly resin finish.  The Rifle has a Magpul front handguard, a shaped and stippled US Palm grip, a trigger/hammer pin retainer plate, an ALG AKT trigger, a Zenit oversized charging handle, Ultimak top rail, the Rifle Dynamics m4 tube stock adapter and a MFT Minimalist stock. 

Having started life as a Saiga, this rifle has the cold hammer forged and chrome lined combloc barrel.  I have only put about 200 rounds through it since I got it back from Rifle Dynamics and they were not corrosive.    I never seem to have the chance to take serious training classes with this gun like I had intended, and it's a shame to see such a beautiful gun just sitting in my safe.


 I am not including the optic you see in the pictures.  It come with the pictured Rifle Dynamics branded case with one Bulgarian Circle 21 Magazine and I have 12 additional magazines I can include for another $200.   I can sell it without the MFT minimalist stock for $50 less if you have another Stock you'd rather use.
